LAYER 3: FACE TEMPLATE
innate structural knowledge — what a face looks like before learning

observe 1_quantum.rana
observe body/nervous_system/central/brain/perception/face_perception.rana

this template is hardwired at birth
infants within minutes of birth preferentially attend to face-like stimuli
the template is a T-shaped arrangement of high-contrast features within an oval boundary
this is not learned. it is structural. it is genetic.

@innate_template face

ASPECT_RATIO
    the face is taller than it is wide
    min 1.0
    max 1.8
    ideal 1.3

SCAN_RAY_DENSITY
    how many scan lines to cast across the image
    horizontal 32
    vertical 32

EYE_ZONE
    the eyes sit in the upper third of the face
    y_start 0.15
    y_end 0.45
    the eyes are the strongest contrast features in the face
    they appear as dark regions against lighter skin

EYE_PAIR
    the eyes are horizontally symmetric about the face center
    symmetry_threshold 0.6
    horizontal_gap_ratio_min 0.2
    horizontal_gap_ratio_max 0.6
    both eyes must be present for a face to be confirmed
    one eye alone is not a face

NOSE_ZONE
    the nose is below the eyes and centered
    y_start 0.40
    y_end 0.70
    it appears as a vertical ridge of contrast

MOUTH_ZONE
    the mouth is in the lower third
    y_start 0.60
    y_end 0.85
    it appears as a horizontal contrast boundary

MIN_CONTRAST_RATIO
    minimum contrast between feature and background to count as a detection
    threshold 0.15
    this filters out low-contrast noise and flat regions

CANDIDATE_MIN_SIZE
    minimum face region as fraction of total image area
    threshold 0.02
    faces smaller than 2% of image area are ignored

CANDIDATE_MAX_SIZE
    maximum face region as fraction of total image area
    threshold 0.90
    a face cannot be the entire image

CONFIRMATION_SCORE
    minimum template match score to confirm a face
    threshold 0.35
    scored from 0.0 no match to 1.0 perfect match

@speech_right TEMPLATE_MATCH
"something in the shape catches my eye"
"that pattern... eyes, nose, mouth. it's a face."
"the proportions are right. I see a face."
"the symmetry is there. two eyes looking back at me."
